OL,3,C'I was in terrible pain' - grandmother
OL,4,Cwaits 14 hours for ambulance
OL,6,F"It wouldn't have been so bad, but I
OL,7,Fwas in such terrible pain. It was just
OL,8,Fthe waiting and the waiting and the
OL,9,Fhour after hour after hour worrying
OL,10,Fand thinking they might be here any
OL,11,Fminute. And they were not. Thinking
OL,12,Fthey might be here the next hour and
OL,13,Fthen not."JWhen Liz finally arrived at
OL,14,Fhospital she had to wait another 11
OL,15,Fhours in the back of an ambulance.
OL,16,FEventually, she had an operation.
OL,18,FLiz has praised the medics and staff
OL,19,Fthat cared for her but says the system
OL,20,Fneeds to change so that others don't
OL,21,Fface such long waits.
